    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-08T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="842"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d842">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">719.00/5–851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Panama</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-08T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 8, 1951—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>359. Pan Chargé called instr Arias request <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>
                    assure <gloss target="#t_CZ1">CZ</gloss> facilities not be used give aid
                    opposition to Govt. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> reiterated position
                    complete neutrality internal matters Pan and requests you bring this attn <gloss
                        target="#t_CZ1">CZ</gloss> civ and mil auths. As <gloss target="#t_Emb1"
                        >Emb</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_CZ1">CZ</gloss> auths of course aware
                    important no expression opinion be given which cld be interpreted encouragement
                    either side.<note n="1" xml:id="d842fn1">In telegram 508, from Panama City, May
                        9, 9 p. m., Chargé Wise reported in part the following: “<gloss
                            target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>’s instructions re non-interference
                        internal matters Pan (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 359, May 8)
                        being strictly observed with full cooperation Gov Newcomer and Gen Morris
                        with whom discussed.” (719.00/5–951)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
